div.p:
ṣadvairi: The six enemies, a mention which appears twice in this inscription, designates the interior enemies of mankind: kāma (the lust), krodha (the anger), lobha (avarice), mada (arrogance), moha (infatuation) and matsara (jealousy). This theme also appears in the K. 834 inscription (st. XXXVIII), and in several Campā inscriptions (see 

            432
          ).

First edited by Abel Bergaigne with a French translation of the Sanskrit part (

            208-232
          ). Edited later by George Coedes (

            3
            175-179
          ) with a French translation of the whole inscription; re-edited here by Chloé Chollet from estampage EFEO n. 997.
